WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:02.267
(light music)

00:02.269 --> 00:04.336
(glass breaks)

00:42.543 --> 00:44.176
(radio stations changing)

00:44.178 --> 00:45.110
- Just pick, that one.

00:45.112 --> 00:45.944
What about now?

00:45.946 --> 00:47.079
Stop, go back two.

00:52.053 --> 00:53.018
No.

00:53.020 --> 00:53.719
- Okay, can you stop stressing?

00:53.721 --> 00:55.087
- Just pick one.

00:55.089 --> 00:56.422
I'm not the one stressing.

01:01.829 --> 01:03.095
- Pretty sure I
see some gray hairs

01:03.097 --> 01:05.264
up in that bird's nest of yours.

01:09.303 --> 01:10.402
- You wanna see a picture?

01:14.475 --> 01:16.875
That's me when I was five.

01:16.877 --> 01:18.243
That's my mom and my dad.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.646
That's where we're going.

01:20.648 --> 01:21.647
It's nice, right?

01:30.558 --> 01:32.791
(sighing)

01:38.199 --> 01:40.432
- How you feelin', baby?

01:40.434 --> 01:41.667
- I feel good.

01:44.405 --> 01:45.270
- How far are we?

01:46.974 --> 01:50.209
- About 20 miles.

01:52.246 --> 01:53.545
(lighter clicking)

01:53.547 --> 01:54.980
- Really?

01:54.982 --> 01:56.315
Come on, again
with those things?

01:56.317 --> 01:57.716
No, we're not doing that.

02:05.226 --> 02:06.391
- Who's that?

02:07.194 --> 02:09.094
Who's that guy?
- Stop.

02:10.164 --> 02:12.364
- Who's, what's his name?

02:12.366 --> 02:13.632
Sean?
- Stop.

02:13.634 --> 02:16.101
- Oh is that Carly's boyfriend?

02:19.006 --> 02:20.038
How are they doin'?

02:22.443 --> 02:25.611
Is she still mad at
him for what he did?

02:25.613 --> 02:26.745
- It's none of your business.

02:27.715 --> 02:29.581
- So who are these people?

02:29.583 --> 02:31.950
- God, just checking
my messages,

02:31.952 --> 02:32.784
calm down.
- How many messages

02:32.786 --> 02:33.685
do you have?

02:36.223 --> 02:37.222
Who's that guy?

02:37.224 --> 02:38.123
- Stop!

02:39.059 --> 02:40.058
- Who is that guy?

02:40.060 --> 02:41.660
- You're being an asshole, stop.

02:44.064 --> 02:45.330
- You know it was a good thing

02:45.332 --> 02:46.532
when I dropped my phone
in the urinal that time.

02:46.534 --> 02:48.567
It was the universe
telling me that

02:48.569 --> 02:49.868
no more phones.

02:49.870 --> 02:51.103
Should never got it fixed.

02:51.105 --> 02:53.272
- You know they do
come in handy, right?

02:53.274 --> 02:56.708
- Oh yeah, they come
in handy, so handy.

02:57.711 --> 02:58.577
- In case of
emergencies, you know,

02:58.579 --> 03:00.245
if your car breaks down.

03:00.247 --> 03:01.947
- For you, there seems
to be an emergency

03:01.949 --> 03:04.983
for like every 10 minutes,

03:04.985 --> 03:09.321
six minute blocks
of 10. (chuckling)

03:09.323 --> 03:11.123
Did you text your
mom I said hello?

03:12.193 --> 03:13.458
- Yes.

03:13.460 --> 03:14.459
- Text her right now,
tell her I said hello.

03:14.461 --> 03:15.460
- She said hello back already.

03:15.462 --> 03:16.295
- I wanna see you text her.

03:16.297 --> 03:17.329
I wanna see.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.265
- No, I'll do it later.
- Right, let me see.

03:20.267 --> 03:21.166
- Really.

03:22.303 --> 03:24.403
Let's just find a
rest stop, go pee

03:24.405 --> 03:25.904
and get to the place.

03:25.906 --> 03:27.239
How about that?

03:28.542 --> 03:30.776
(revving)

03:49.697 --> 03:51.563
- Bathroom's that way.

03:51.565 --> 03:54.199
- [Woman] Cool, I think I'm
gonna go call my mom, okay?

03:54.201 --> 03:55.100
- Okay.

04:05.379 --> 04:08.247
(zipping)

04:08.249 --> 04:12.751
(trickling)
(toilet flushing)

04:12.753 --> 04:15.153
(splashing)

04:33.540 --> 04:35.874
(slamming)

04:54.128 --> 04:55.794
- [Woman] What's wrong?

04:55.796 --> 04:58.196
- Which way did that car go?

04:58.198 --> 04:59.431
The guy that came out

04:59.433 --> 05:00.932
like two, three
seconds before me.

05:00.934 --> 05:01.867
This was his car.

05:03.704 --> 05:04.970
Where, they beam him up?

05:04.972 --> 05:06.338
What, this makes no sense.

05:06.340 --> 05:08.073
- Baby I didn't see a guy.

05:08.075 --> 05:09.641
I mean I was on my phone.

05:10.944 --> 05:12.678
So maybe I missed
him, I don't know.

05:17.518 --> 05:19.751
- That is so weird.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.021
- Don't worry
about it, let's go.

05:23.023 --> 05:23.855
Come back to the car.
- Wait a minute.

05:23.857 --> 05:24.756
No, stop, stop.

05:26.026 --> 05:26.858
Well you were standing there.

05:29.496 --> 05:30.312
Which way did he go?

05:30.313 --> 05:31.129
- I don't know, what
did he look like?

05:31.131 --> 05:32.230
- The black car,
when we pulled in,

05:32.232 --> 05:33.432
there was a black car

05:33.434 --> 05:34.366
in here.
- I didn't see a black car.

05:34.368 --> 05:35.667
I probably just missed it

05:35.669 --> 05:36.868
'cause I was on my phone.

05:36.870 --> 05:38.437
Don't worry about it,
let's go, come on.

05:39.540 --> 05:41.440
- Oh so you admit that
you were on your phone.

05:41.442 --> 05:42.407
That's the problem.

05:42.409 --> 05:43.675
- Yes, I admit that I was

05:43.677 --> 05:44.676
on my phone, Billy.
- Yeah, let's.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.345
Hi, my name's Lisa Text.

05:46.347 --> 05:47.579
- Wow, you're gonna do

05:47.581 --> 05:48.747
this again?
- Got your head in the phone.

05:48.749 --> 05:49.848
- Seriously, let's go.
- You're texting.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.083
You can't even see a car
- Okay Billy.

05:51.085 --> 05:51.883
- that's two feet
in front of you.

05:51.885 --> 05:53.118
'Cause you're texting.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.587
I'm texting my mom,
I'm texting my sister.

05:55.589 --> 05:57.356
I'm texting, texting, texting.

06:02.196 --> 06:03.512
Texting.

06:03.513 --> 06:04.829
That's why you don't
drive, that's why.

06:04.832 --> 06:06.898
(slamming)

06:06.900 --> 06:10.268
This is a big problem between
the both of us right now.

06:10.270 --> 06:12.904
(car starting)

06:15.075 --> 06:17.309
(revving)

06:27.054 --> 06:29.121
- It's supposed to
rain all weekend.

06:29.123 --> 06:30.655
- It's sunny out now.

06:30.657 --> 06:32.190
Why don't you keep it upbeat?

06:32.993 --> 06:34.326
How about that?

06:35.496 --> 06:37.162
(sighing)

06:37.164 --> 06:39.731
(tense music)

07:17.371 --> 07:19.004
It's been here since
I was six years old,

07:19.006 --> 07:20.338
exactly in the same spot.

07:21.642 --> 07:24.242
It's genuine cedar wood.

07:25.612 --> 07:26.711
See how smooth

07:26.713 --> 07:27.546
that second hand moves?
- Come on now

07:27.548 --> 07:28.647
let's go check in, babe.

07:28.649 --> 07:30.182
Let's go, keep going.

07:31.552 --> 07:33.618
- Mhmm, uh huh.

07:34.555 --> 07:37.589
Mhmmm.
(bell ringing)

07:37.591 --> 07:39.291
- So are you winning?

07:39.293 --> 07:40.625
- Certainly not.

07:40.627 --> 07:42.828
So are you checking in?

07:42.830 --> 07:44.262
- Yes we are indeed.

07:44.264 --> 07:45.197
- Well that's great.

07:45.199 --> 07:47.666
For the weekend or for a week?

07:47.668 --> 07:49.000
- Weekend.

07:49.002 --> 07:49.835
- Uh huh.

07:49.837 --> 07:50.802
- This is Lisa.

07:50.804 --> 07:52.037
- Hi Lisa.
- I'm Billy.

07:52.039 --> 07:52.938
Yeah I used to come
here when I was a kid.

07:52.940 --> 07:55.040
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

07:55.042 --> 07:57.809
- Do you have your
driver's license with you?

08:00.781 --> 08:01.680
Ah.

08:02.816 --> 08:06.151
Billy Curtis, hmm.

08:06.153 --> 08:10.121
- Yeah.
- Brooklyn, New York, yes.

08:10.123 --> 08:12.123
So that's quite a jog down here.

08:13.193 --> 08:14.326
What's the occasion?

08:16.063 --> 08:17.896
- Well, there's no occasion.

08:17.898 --> 08:19.698
You know, we're trying to
get away from the city.

08:19.700 --> 08:20.932
- Uh huh.

08:20.934 --> 08:24.970
- Come here, breathe
fresh air and,

08:24.972 --> 08:25.871
- And?
- And

08:25.873 --> 08:27.639
here we are.

08:27.641 --> 08:30.008
- Well, great.

08:30.010 --> 08:33.712
And I'm Frederick, not Fred.

08:33.714 --> 08:36.081
I am the innkeeper

08:36.083 --> 08:39.518
and it's very nice
to meet both of you.

08:39.520 --> 08:41.720
- Nice to meet you too.
- Good to meet you too.

08:41.722 --> 08:43.955
- So how long have you
been the innkeeper here,

08:43.957 --> 08:45.290
Frederick?
- Hmm, wow.

08:47.261 --> 08:50.061
It's 30 years, maybe
a little longer.

08:51.265 --> 08:52.764
Would you have a
credit card with you?

08:52.766 --> 08:54.366
- Yes.

08:54.368 --> 08:56.067
- Oh, thank you.

08:56.069 --> 08:58.003
It will be encrypted,
not to worry.

09:02.609 --> 09:03.909
Okay good.

09:03.911 --> 09:08.146
Now checkout will be
11 a.m. on Monday.

09:08.148 --> 09:09.481
And if you need
anything, by all means

09:09.483 --> 09:11.516
just buzz down here
to the front desk

09:11.518 --> 09:15.921
and usually be myself or
Victor the night manager.

09:15.923 --> 09:17.155
- Victor, okay.

09:17.157 --> 09:21.259
- Yes, and I have
you in room two.

09:21.261 --> 09:22.193
- Cool.

09:22.195 --> 09:24.029
- Two flights up, down the hall,

09:24.031 --> 09:26.631
you might remember
from your youth.

09:26.633 --> 09:28.633
- No, I mean I
wouldn't remember.

09:28.635 --> 09:30.969
I know that I came
here when I was a kid.

09:30.971 --> 09:32.470
I just know that my
parents took me here,

09:32.472 --> 09:33.672
here and the Elson Inn.

09:34.541 --> 09:37.175
- Ah, the Elson Inn.

09:37.177 --> 09:39.978
Yes, they tore it
down a few years ago.

09:39.980 --> 09:42.547
It was in terrible condition.

09:42.549 --> 09:45.050
And it was the oldest
inn on the island.

09:45.052 --> 09:46.484
(chuckling)

09:46.486 --> 09:48.119
- I hate it when they tear
down those old places.

09:48.121 --> 09:50.488
- Yeah well that's the
charm of this town, is it?

09:50.490 --> 09:53.291
They usually don't tear
down old landmarks.

09:53.293 --> 09:55.961
They do the very best they
can to restore them, but,

09:56.930 --> 10:00.332
time, it does take its toll.

10:00.334 --> 10:01.232
- Yeah.

10:02.970 --> 10:05.804
- So we don't have many
guests this weekend.

10:05.806 --> 10:08.306
Not yet, you know,
the weekend is young.

10:09.610 --> 10:12.344
But you never know,
things might just pick up.

10:12.346 --> 10:14.412
You never know what
tomorrow will bring.

10:15.649 --> 10:19.451
And I hope you
have a very, very,

10:19.453 --> 10:20.819
- Hup, thank you.
- Here it is.

10:20.821 --> 10:21.786
Ah, there you are,

10:21.788 --> 10:23.655
pleasant stay.
- Thank you.

10:23.657 --> 10:24.789
- Thank you.
- Two flights up,

10:24.791 --> 10:25.757
down the hall.
- Wonderful.

10:25.759 --> 10:27.392
- Welcome to use the phone.

10:27.394 --> 10:30.462
- So wonderful to meet you.
- Thanks.

10:35.268 --> 10:36.701
- That was weird.

10:36.703 --> 10:38.436
- Well it's weird,
everything's weird.

10:38.438 --> 10:39.671
Everything.

10:39.673 --> 10:41.272
The rest stop's weird,
car ride's weird.

10:41.274 --> 10:42.240
- No, the whole thing I guess,

10:42.242 --> 10:43.575
I just hope we have a nice stay.

10:43.577 --> 10:44.909
- What do you mean
the whole thing?

10:44.911 --> 10:46.711
The whole thing?

10:46.713 --> 10:48.113
What's wrong, what do you mean?

10:48.115 --> 10:49.347
What happened to
having a great time?

10:49.349 --> 10:50.615
- Are you sure we
have the right place?

10:50.617 --> 10:51.516
- No, we got the wrong
place, can't you see?

10:51.518 --> 10:52.417
It's shabby chic.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.388
You know, you're just
high maintenance, see.

10:56.390 --> 10:58.123
It's 145 years old.

11:01.294 --> 11:02.961
You're just very used
to what you're used to

11:02.963 --> 11:06.498
and anything that's out of
the ordinary is a problem.

11:07.868 --> 11:09.534
Towels on the floor.

11:09.536 --> 11:10.969
Maybe the maid has off.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.003
- [Lisa] You think?

11:15.509 --> 11:16.341
- Are you mad at me
because I told you

11:16.343 --> 11:17.509
that there'd be wifi?

11:17.511 --> 11:18.576
- [Lisa] No.

11:39.232 --> 11:40.732
- Is this all right?

11:42.235 --> 11:43.134
- Yeah.

11:44.671 --> 11:46.571
It's good to get out of town.

11:46.573 --> 11:48.106
It's a good change of scenery.

11:50.410 --> 11:53.211
And I really liked
seeing all the trees

11:53.213 --> 11:54.412
on the drive down here.

11:55.949 --> 11:57.482
- And you gotta come
with me in the fall

11:57.484 --> 11:59.684
so you can see all
the pretty colors.

11:59.686 --> 12:03.455
(bag zipping and clattering)

12:04.291 --> 12:06.925
- You know what I think?

12:06.927 --> 12:09.627
I think that you
miss being down here.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.501
- City burns me out, man.

12:16.503 --> 12:17.802
City burns me out.

12:19.172 --> 12:21.005
You handle city
better than I do.

12:23.243 --> 12:25.076
(groaning)

12:25.078 --> 12:25.944
- I don't know about that.

12:25.946 --> 12:27.178
- [Billy] Yeah?

12:27.180 --> 12:29.347
- Maybe just hide
it better than you.

12:29.349 --> 12:34.419
- Yeah I'm more like
plaid, stripes and wool.

12:35.455 --> 12:39.224
And you're more satin
and silk, black.

12:40.560 --> 12:44.629
- That's me, you
nailed it. (chuckling)

12:49.236 --> 12:50.769
- [Billy] Okay, that was odd.

12:50.771 --> 12:51.636
- What?

13:00.247 --> 13:02.881
- I was just about
to pack the drawer.

13:02.883 --> 13:04.849
It was open when
we came in here.

13:07.053 --> 13:08.119
And now it's closed.

13:09.422 --> 13:13.525
I was emptying my suitcase,
loading up the drawer

13:13.527 --> 13:14.692
and I turned around

13:14.694 --> 13:16.928
and it was closed.
- You know what I think?

13:16.930 --> 13:19.798
I think that you need
something to eat.

13:21.334 --> 13:22.767
- No, it has nothing
to do with me

13:22.769 --> 13:23.868
needing something to eat.

13:23.870 --> 13:25.503
The drawer was open.

13:28.041 --> 13:29.741
I turn around, now it's closed.

13:30.610 --> 13:32.811
- Okay so you're saying that

13:32.813 --> 13:35.713
that thing just
closed on its own?

13:36.850 --> 13:38.750
- Yeah, maybe.

13:44.991 --> 13:47.559
I'm going for a walk.

13:47.561 --> 13:49.928
- You want me to join you?

13:49.930 --> 13:54.132
- [Billy] No.

13:54.134 --> 13:57.468
- [Wispy Voice] Get
out of here, Billy.

14:10.984 --> 14:14.219
(lightly tense music)

14:27.767 --> 14:29.234
- That happens all the time.

14:31.238 --> 14:32.136
It falls.

14:33.006 --> 14:33.905
- Oh.

14:35.108 --> 14:36.975
I'm Billy from down the hall.

14:36.977 --> 14:38.710
- Hey, Billy from down the hall.

14:39.779 --> 14:40.612
Wait, wait, wait,

14:40.614 --> 14:41.546
Billy, Billy, Billy.

14:41.548 --> 14:42.547
Come and have a drink with me.

14:42.549 --> 14:43.448
Come here.

14:44.217 --> 14:45.450
I hate drinking alone.

14:50.757 --> 14:52.724
- I'm just good, thank you.

14:52.726 --> 14:53.625
- No.

14:57.998 --> 15:00.064
What should we drink to?

15:00.066 --> 15:01.599
- Strangers.

15:01.601 --> 15:03.268
- [Man] I'll drink to strangers.

15:06.706 --> 15:07.605
- You a writer?

15:08.842 --> 15:10.308
- Yeah.

15:10.310 --> 15:11.276
I was.

15:12.445 --> 15:13.378
I suppose.

15:14.481 --> 15:15.480
I wrote this.

15:17.317 --> 15:19.017
30 years ago in this room.

15:21.721 --> 15:22.787
It's an old book.

15:24.758 --> 15:26.024
Well I'm back here.

15:27.027 --> 15:28.660
Maybe I can write another one.

15:33.667 --> 15:35.300
Come here, give me.

15:35.302 --> 15:36.401
Give it back.

15:36.403 --> 15:37.735
You don't need.

15:40.240 --> 15:41.839
- [Billy] You wrote
that 30 years ago?

15:41.841 --> 15:42.740
- Yeah.

15:44.477 --> 15:45.843
Right in this room

15:47.247 --> 15:48.546
and with that typewriter.

15:49.983 --> 15:51.082
- That's 1986.

15:51.084 --> 15:53.351
- 1986, yeah.

15:54.654 --> 15:56.287
Probably when you were how old?

15:58.825 --> 15:59.958
- Six.

15:59.960 --> 16:01.893
- Long time ago, huh?

16:01.895 --> 16:03.394
- Yeah.

16:03.396 --> 16:05.163
- I think I'm back
here so I could

16:07.067 --> 16:11.102
maybe tap in whatever
that magic was.

16:12.839 --> 16:15.139
Hell, maybe you're
part of the magic.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.407
What are you doing here?

16:17.410 --> 16:18.643
- I'm here with my girlfriend.

16:18.645 --> 16:19.444
- Yeah?

16:19.446 --> 16:20.611
What's her name?

16:20.613 --> 16:22.580
- Lisa.
- Lisa?

16:22.582 --> 16:23.514
Are you in love?

16:26.486 --> 16:28.152
- I don't know.

16:28.154 --> 16:30.054
- You don't know?

16:30.056 --> 16:31.823
Love is a beautiful thing.

16:32.926 --> 16:34.892
Well you'll have to
bring Lisa back up

16:34.894 --> 16:35.860
and have a drink with me.

16:35.862 --> 16:37.161
Will you do that?

16:37.163 --> 16:38.496
- That's a possibility.

16:44.904 --> 16:47.038
(exhaling)

16:47.040 --> 16:48.573
Wow, that just really hit me.

16:50.610 --> 16:51.576
- Are you okay?

16:51.578 --> 16:53.044
- Yeah.

16:53.046 --> 16:56.981
I just gotta get back
to my girlfriend.

16:58.018 --> 16:59.784
I'm gonna head out.

17:00.987 --> 17:03.087
But thanks for inviting
me into your place,

17:03.089 --> 17:04.956
appreciate that, and the drink.

17:06.726 --> 17:07.625
- [Writer] Nice
meeting you, Billy.

17:07.627 --> 17:09.494
- Nice meeting you too.

17:09.496 --> 17:11.262
- Come back, all right?

17:11.264 --> 17:12.163
With Lisa though.

17:13.366 --> 17:15.366
Only with Lisa.

17:27.280 --> 17:29.514
(sighing)

17:41.294 --> 17:43.594
(creaking)

17:46.666 --> 17:48.433
- [Lisa] Everything all right?

17:48.435 --> 17:49.333
- Yeah.

17:50.970 --> 17:51.869
It's good.

17:56.176 --> 17:57.809
That guy was weird.

17:59.345 --> 18:00.244
- What's weird?

18:01.614 --> 18:03.981
- This writer, I met this
writer down the hallway.

18:03.983 --> 18:05.850
He's really strange.

18:09.789 --> 18:10.688
- Hmm.

18:11.825 --> 18:15.293
- He like invited
me to his room.

18:18.498 --> 18:20.665
And he like made me a
drink and he's talking.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.301
It's really strange.

18:24.637 --> 18:27.205
- Baby, is that what
you're wearing to dinner?

18:29.876 --> 18:31.242
