Just under the bed.

46:44.602 --> 46:45.735
- Did you show your girlfriend?

46:45.737 --> 46:46.636
- [Billy] No.

46:47.539 --> 46:49.038
- Why not?

46:49.040 --> 46:51.340
- Because it was horrific and
I didn't want to scare her.

46:55.680 --> 46:57.413
(sighing)

46:57.415 --> 46:59.916
- Look, Billy.

47:01.286 --> 47:02.752
There's not much more I can do

47:02.754 --> 47:04.921
until I see this tape.

47:04.923 --> 47:06.088
- (sighing) No,
I understand that

47:06.090 --> 47:08.057
but this doesn't ring a bell,

47:08.059 --> 47:09.859
or it's not familiar?

47:09.861 --> 47:12.962
A murdered couple, you've
never heard that before?

47:13.865 --> 47:15.131
- I can't say that it does.

47:15.133 --> 47:18.000
I mean, this is a
small resort town.

47:18.002 --> 47:20.770
We got three detectives,
uniformed police.

47:21.873 --> 47:24.373
There's not a lot
of crime, you know.

47:24.375 --> 47:26.142
I mean in the summers we got

47:27.245 --> 47:28.711
kids that are getting
rowdy in the clubs,

47:28.713 --> 47:31.280
you know, breaking up
fights, things like that.

47:31.282 --> 47:33.449
There's a car or a house
that gets broken into

47:33.451 --> 47:37.420
but other than that it's
a really quiet town.

47:37.422 --> 47:39.222
- So no murders?

47:39.224 --> 47:41.824
- (chuckling) No, no murders.

47:41.826 --> 47:44.193
I mean, not that I'm aware of.

47:44.195 --> 47:46.762
I've only been in this
precinct a very short time.

47:49.267 --> 47:53.102
(sighing) But anyhow.

47:54.873 --> 47:55.771
Here's my card.

47:58.877 --> 48:02.511
If you find the videotape,
just let me know.

48:03.615 --> 48:05.114
- Okay.

48:05.116 --> 48:07.250
I'm sorry I had you come here

48:07.252 --> 48:09.352
and waste your time, Detective.

48:09.354 --> 48:11.254
I appreciate it.

48:11.256 --> 48:13.055
- You didn't waste my time.

48:13.057 --> 48:15.258
Try to enjoy the
rest of your stay.

48:15.260 --> 48:16.158
- I'll try.

48:19.430 --> 48:22.164
(door creaking)

48:26.704 --> 48:31.507
- No, I'm happy to hold a
reservation for 48 hours.

48:31.509 --> 48:33.843
No, the pleasure's always mine.

48:35.680 --> 48:36.579
Goodbye.

48:40.618 --> 48:43.419
(floor creaking)

48:46.157 --> 48:48.024
Ah, Billy.

48:48.860 --> 48:50.726
I hope everything's all right.

48:50.728 --> 48:53.195
- No, it's not all right.

48:54.232 --> 48:55.331
- What's the problem?

48:56.668 --> 48:57.566
- Well.

49:00.238 --> 49:04.607
There's a tape that's
missing from my room.

49:04.609 --> 49:06.375
- A tape?
- A video tape.

49:07.612 --> 49:09.745
So what about it?
- I found a video tape

49:09.747 --> 49:11.347
in my room.

49:11.349 --> 49:13.049
And now it's gone missing.

49:13.051 --> 49:13.883
- Missing?

49:13.885 --> 49:14.784
- Yes.

49:16.587 --> 49:18.688
- Well I don't know
how to help you.

49:20.224 --> 49:22.224
It's barely 10 a.m.

49:22.226 --> 49:23.459
No one's been in your room.

49:23.461 --> 49:24.660
- No one has come in my room?

49:24.662 --> 49:26.262
- No.

49:26.264 --> 49:27.163
- No one?

49:27.165 --> 49:27.997
- No, of course it's--

49:27.999 --> 49:29.031
- Not even a maid?

49:29.834 --> 49:31.300
- We have a maid, it's Peggy,

49:31.302 --> 49:34.437
but she doesn't
come too much later

49:34.439 --> 49:36.572
till after checkout time.

49:36.574 --> 49:38.874
And even after that,

49:40.278 --> 49:44.680
she changes the linen and
brings fresh towels, yes,

49:44.682 --> 49:47.283
but she won't be
over quite some time.

49:48.753 --> 49:51.187
Billy, I'm sorry, I don't
think I can help you.

50:14.912 --> 50:17.146
(sighing)

50:34.832 --> 50:35.898
- Am I late?

50:37.902 --> 50:40.069
- It's 10:30, where were you?

50:45.276 --> 50:46.509
- Why don't you give me a break

50:46.511 --> 50:47.910
and let's have some fun?

50:49.680 --> 50:52.014
- Yay, I'm all for fun.

50:54.685 --> 50:56.185
- Let's have a good
time, you know?

51:00.158 --> 51:01.791
What do you wanna do?

51:01.793 --> 51:03.025
- I don't know, Billy.

51:03.027 --> 51:04.160
You're the tour
guide, you tell me.

51:05.463 --> 51:07.063
What are we gonna do?

51:09.801 --> 51:11.434
- I say we take a ride into town

51:11.436 --> 51:13.569
and then hot chocolate and then
we'll go to the lighthouse.

51:18.709 --> 51:19.942
- [Lisa] Okay.

51:39.530 --> 51:41.864
(coughing)

51:43.501 --> 51:45.734
(sighing)

51:49.740 --> 51:52.908
(somber music)

51:52.910 --> 51:55.211
(giggling)

52:04.989 --> 52:06.856
- Where are you going?

52:26.010 --> 52:30.646
- We have just taken 228
steps to get up here.

52:30.648 --> 52:33.449
The lighthouse is a
total of 171 feet.

52:34.519 --> 52:36.886
Now some of you may
know of the SS Atlantis

52:36.888 --> 52:39.321
but if you look far
enough to the south,

52:39.323 --> 52:41.090
you'll spot a piece of the hull

52:41.092 --> 52:43.726
from the obscure
Sir Edmond James

52:43.728 --> 52:47.496
which fell victim to a
shipwreck here in 1899.

52:47.498 --> 52:49.798
It was on its way to
China carrying freight

52:49.800 --> 52:51.767
when it ran into a dense fog

52:51.769 --> 52:54.904
which ultimately
led to its demise.

52:54.906 --> 52:56.305
- Wow.

52:56.307 --> 52:58.440
Were there any survivors?

52:58.442 --> 52:59.942
- As a matter of fact, yes.

52:59.944 --> 53:03.112
The Captain, Edward Louis
was the only survivor.

53:03.114 --> 53:05.381
The rest of his
crew, nine men total,

53:05.383 --> 53:06.849
met their fate that night.

53:06.851 --> 53:07.750
- Wow.

53:08.953 --> 53:10.986
What happened to the Captain?

53:10.988 --> 53:12.254
- Funny you mentioned.

53:12.256 --> 53:13.756
He swam ashore and was
nursed back to health

53:13.758 --> 53:14.990
at the Doctor's Inn

53:14.992 --> 53:16.559
which was the first
place he stumbled upon

53:16.561 --> 53:17.960
on that rainy night.

53:17.962 --> 53:21.764
A few years later, he
became the innkeeper there.

53:21.766 --> 53:23.199
- Great, we're staying
at the Doctor's Inn.

53:23.201 --> 53:25.601
- Well, it's a lovely place.

53:25.603 --> 53:27.836
But it certainly has a history.

53:27.838 --> 53:29.305
- What kind of history?

53:29.307 --> 53:31.840
- Some say there are some
haunted areas in town,

53:31.842 --> 53:33.809
the Doctor's Inn
being one of them.

53:33.811 --> 53:34.677
- Are there any others?

53:34.679 --> 53:36.612
- Oh there are several.

53:37.715 --> 53:40.282
There's a ghost tour
if you're interested.

53:40.284 --> 53:42.051
- Oh god, I love ghost tours.

53:42.053 --> 53:44.486
- No, I don't wanna, no.

53:44.488 --> 53:45.955
I'm not gonna go
on a ghost tour.

53:45.957 --> 53:47.156
- I'm gonna keep this.
- I don't think so.

53:47.158 --> 53:49.959
I don't wanna go
to a ghost tour.

53:56.367 --> 53:58.133
Thanks for showing
us the lighthouse.

53:58.135 --> 53:59.635
- My pleasure.

53:59.637 --> 54:01.637
- You must really love it
to walk up all those stairs.

54:01.639 --> 54:02.638
- Yeah.

54:02.640 --> 54:04.440
I'm a real people person.

54:04.442 --> 54:06.775
Plus the stairs give
me a good workout.

54:06.777 --> 54:09.078
- So how long you've
been doing this for?

54:09.080 --> 54:10.412
- Let's see.

54:10.414 --> 54:13.282
I've been here part
time after I got out

54:13.284 --> 54:15.684
of the service in 1981.

54:15.686 --> 54:17.152
- [Billy] What, the Navy?

54:19.156 --> 54:19.788
- That's right.

54:19.789 --> 54:20.421
I've had some odd
jobs over the years

54:20.424 --> 54:22.891
but I've been here
full time since 1995.

54:22.893 --> 54:24.026
- That's a long time.

54:28.332 --> 54:31.967
Let me ask you, did you
really believe in this

54:31.969 --> 54:33.302
ghost stuff, like?

54:33.304 --> 54:35.104
Is the Doctor's
Inn really haunted?

54:35.973 --> 54:37.172
- It's folklore.

54:38.309 --> 54:40.175
It's also part of the tour.

54:40.177 --> 54:41.410
Helps the economy.

54:41.412 --> 54:43.112
People like that sort of thing.

54:43.114 --> 54:44.146
- That makes sense.

54:45.249 --> 54:46.282
My parents used
to bring me there

54:46.284 --> 54:48.183
when I was little.

54:48.185 --> 54:49.718
- So beautiful.

54:49.720 --> 54:52.421
Charles, are there
any bathrooms up here?

54:52.423 --> 54:55.024
- [Charles] Oh, sure, let
me take you down there.

54:55.026 --> 54:56.592
- Okay.

54:56.594 --> 54:58.060
- [Charles] Watch your step.

55:01.866 --> 55:03.098
So how long will you be staying

55:03.100 --> 55:04.733
at the Doctor's Inn?

55:04.735 --> 55:06.602
- Like three days.

55:06.604 --> 55:11.473
We just got here yesterday.

55:11.475 --> 55:13.309
Ooh, we got new towels, baby.

55:14.745 --> 55:16.278
- Oh, I love fresh towels.

55:18.883 --> 55:22.051
- I am going to take a bath.

55:22.053 --> 55:23.585
- No, no, take a shower.

55:23.587 --> 55:24.853
Take a bath later.

55:24.855 --> 55:26.822
Just rinse off, no ordeal.

55:26.824 --> 55:28.724
- [Lisa] Fine.

55:28.726 --> 55:30.859
Hey baby, where are
we gonna go eat?

55:31.996 --> 55:33.896
- I feel like seafood.

55:33.898 --> 55:34.897
(tense music)

55:34.899 --> 55:36.131
- [Lisa] Okay.

55:52.583 --> 55:54.016
(knocking)

55:54.018 --> 55:55.250
- [Billy] I'll be back.

55:56.153 --> 55:57.052
- Billy.

55:57.955 --> 56:00.522
(tense music)

56:10.034 --> 56:11.400
(sighing)

56:11.402 --> 56:13.268
- Detective, I got the tape!

56:14.205 --> 56:15.504
I got the tape.

56:16.974 --> 56:18.040
- Hey listen, Billy.

56:19.176 --> 56:20.109
I'm done for the day.

56:20.111 --> 56:21.577
I'm just about to leave, okay?

56:21.579 --> 56:23.379
- It's the tape.

56:23.381 --> 56:24.980
- It's after five.

56:24.982 --> 56:26.415
- Please.

56:26.417 --> 56:28.217
This is the tape, please.

56:29.320 --> 56:30.919
- All right, all
right, come on in.

56:43.868 --> 56:46.835
So, where'd you find the tape?

56:46.837 --> 56:47.736
- It popped up.

56:50.474 --> 56:52.574
I'm telling you
Detective, it popped up.

56:53.444 --> 56:54.376
- Popped up, huh?

56:54.378 --> 56:55.844
- Right in the dresser drawer.

57:00.351 --> 57:01.683
I'm telling you, there's
a lot of weird stuff

57:01.685 --> 57:03.252
going on right now, Detective.

57:04.188 --> 57:06.221
- Okay, well let's have a look.

57:10.327 --> 57:12.561
(sighing)

57:16.634 --> 57:18.867
(sighing)

57:23.541 --> 57:25.474
What's going on,
where's the picture?

57:26.610 --> 57:27.810
- Press forward.

57:27.812 --> 57:28.944
- [Mueller] I'm
fast forwarding it.

57:30.114 --> 57:31.013
- Press play.

57:31.949 --> 57:33.215
- Look.

57:33.217 --> 57:34.683
I'm pressing rewind,

57:34.685 --> 57:35.617
fast forward.
- I don't know.

57:35.619 --> 57:36.952
I'm not making it up, Detective.

57:36.954 --> 57:38.020
- I'm pressing play.

57:38.022 --> 57:39.254
This is crazy, Billy.
- I know.

57:39.256 --> 57:40.622
I put it on there,
I saw the tape,

57:40.624 --> 57:41.557
I saw with my own eyes.

57:41.559 --> 57:42.791
Why would I make it up?

57:45.196 --> 57:46.361
(sighing)

57:46.363 --> 57:47.930
I don't know, I don't know.

57:47.932 --> 57:49.298
- Just take it easy, okay?

57:54.438 --> 57:56.004
Tell me again what happened.

57:56.006 --> 57:57.673
- I picked up my
girlfriend at the cafe,

57:57.675 --> 57:59.641
we went down to, we
walked around the town,

57:59.643 --> 58:00.576
we went to the lighthouse.

58:00.578 --> 58:01.844
We came back to the hotel.

58:01.846 --> 58:03.545
We talked about getting
dinner, go for a drive.

58:03.547 --> 58:05.147
She went and took a bath,
I opened up the drawer

58:05.149 --> 58:06.448
and there it was.

58:06.450 --> 58:07.816
The tape was just
sitting right there.

58:10.154 --> 58:11.053
- Hmm.

58:13.257 --> 58:15.324
Are you suggesting that
someone's playing tricks on you?

58:15.326 --> 58:17.526
- Personally,
maybe, I don't know.

58:17.528 --> 58:18.727
It's the same tape.

58:19.563 --> 58:20.929
- Really?

58:20.931 --> 58:22.297
How do you know
it's the same tape?

58:22.299 --> 58:23.198
Did you look at it
before coming here?

58:23.200 --> 58:24.233
- No I didn't.

58:26.270 --> 58:27.169
- Hmm.

58:29.540 --> 58:30.506
Tell me something.

58:31.842 --> 58:33.275
Does your girlfriend
know anything about this?

58:33.277 --> 58:35.277
- No, I'm the only one
who knows about this.

58:35.279 --> 58:36.545
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

58:39.750 --> 58:41.183
- Is your girlfriend
back at the inn?

58:41.185 --> 58:42.084
- [Billy] Yes.

58:50.060 --> 58:50.993
- Jack?
- Detective.

58:50.995 --> 58:52.427
- Hey, just hold on a second.

58:52.429 --> 58:54.263
Hey Jack, do me a favor.

58:54.265 --> 58:55.631
Could you go to the Doctor's Inn

58:55.633 --> 58:57.900
and pick up a Lisa,

58:57.902 --> 58:58.934
- Morris.

58:58.936 --> 59:00.135
- Lisa Morris.

59:00.137 --> 59:02.804
She's on the second
floor, room two.

59:02.806 --> 59:04.006
Yeah, that's right.

59:05.576 --> 59:07.843
Yes, right away, thanks.

59:15.586 --> 59:18.320
(sign creaking)

59:23.427 --> 59:25.060
Lisa?

59:25.062 --> 59:26.361
I'm Detective Mueller.

59:26.363 --> 59:28.263
- Nice to meet you.
- Thanks for coming.

59:28.265 --> 59:29.197
- Is Billy okay?

59:29.199 --> 59:30.132
- Yeah, he's all right.

59:30.134 --> 59:31.366
Can I get you some coffee?

59:31.368 --> 59:33.402
- No, I'm good, thank you.

59:33.404 --> 59:34.603
- Okay.

59:34.605 --> 59:37.039
Yeah, he's fine, he's
in the next room.

59:37.041 --> 59:38.173
- Okay.

59:38.175 --> 59:40.008
What's this about?

59:40.010 --> 59:41.810
- Well, your boyfriend
called me this morning

59:41.812 --> 59:45.013
and he told me he
found a videotape.

59:45.950 --> 59:48.016
You know anything about this?

59:48.018 --> 59:48.884
- No.

59:52.089 --> 59:53.055
- Okay, well,

59:54.158 --> 59:56.124
things he told me
on this videotape

59:56.126 --> 59:57.192
are pretty gruesome.

59:59.363 --> 1:00:02.197
Evidently, a couple gets killed.

1:00:02.199 --> 1:00:03.398
And it's like a home movie,

1:00:03.400 --> 1:00:04.566
two guys filming it.

1:00:05.970 --> 1:00:07.469
I mean he was very detailed
with what he told me

1:00:07.471 --> 1:00:09.204
and it sounded very believable.

1:00:11.976 --> 1:00:13.575
He's pretty shaken up.

1:00:14.912 --> 1:00:17.145
He brought the tape over
just as I was about to leave

1:00:17.147 --> 1:00:18.213
for the day, and,

1:00:19.483 --> 1:00:20.882
when we popped the tape in,

1:00:22.453 --> 1:00:23.885
there was nothing on there.

1:00:24.855 --> 1:00:27.489
It's completely blank.

1:00:27.491 --> 1:00:28.390
- That's crazy.

1:00:29.360 --> 1:00:30.258
- Yeah, I'll say.

1:00:32.262 --> 1:00:35.063
Anyhow, that's why I
asked you to come here.

1:00:37.935 --> 1:00:39.801
Lisa, how long have
you been dating?

1:00:42.740 --> 1:00:44.806
- Like a little
less than a year.

1:00:48.278 --> 1:00:49.444
- And how did you meet?

1:00:51.015 --> 1:00:52.280
- We had mutual
friends that worked

1:00:52.282 --> 1:00:54.950
at a bar together
in our neighborhood.

1:00:54.952 --> 1:00:56.485
- And then you started dating?

1:00:57.287 --> 1:00:59.021
- Yeah, pretty much.

1:00:59.023 --> 1:00:59.888
- Okay.

1:01:02.793 --> 1:01:05.160
Do you know anything
about his background?

1:01:05.162 --> 1:01:06.194
- Not much.

1:01:06.196 --> 1:01:07.229
I just know that
his parents died

1:01:07.231 --> 1:01:08.530
when he was really young.

1:01:09.333 --> 1:01:10.232
- Uh huh.

1:01:12.202 --> 1:01:14.803
- And he hadn't been back since.

1:01:15.706 --> 1:01:17.506
This meant a lot to him.

1:01:21.045 --> 1:01:22.511
It was rough.

1:01:23.681 --> 1:01:25.881
You know, we don't get
out of the city much.

1:01:27.451 --> 1:01:28.350
- I see.

1:01:29.987 --> 1:01:31.453
Do you know how
his parents died?

1:01:33.290 --> 1:01:34.890
- No, I don't.

1:01:34.892 --> 1:01:36.658
Again, he doesn't
really say much.

1:01:37.761 --> 1:01:39.561
I just know that it was,

1:01:39.563 --> 1:01:42.330
I just know that it was
really really painful for him.

1:01:43.667 --> 1:01:45.033
- Any idea who raised him?

1:01:45.969 --> 1:01:46.968
- I think his aunt.

1:01:48.372 --> 1:01:50.272
Again, he doesn't say much.

1:01:50.274 --> 1:01:51.840
Just bits and pieces, you know?

1:01:54.378 --> 1:01:55.243
- Hmm.

1:01:59.316 --> 1:02:00.348
Is he on medication?

1:02:03.153 --> 1:02:04.086
I have to ask.

1:02:05.622 --> 1:02:07.322
- Yes, he is.

1:02:09.126 --> 1:02:11.293
But I don't know the
name of it, though.

1:02:16.366 --> 1:02:18.700
- (sighing) Oh, man.

1:02:20.137 --> 1:02:21.503
This is a tough one, Lisa.

1:02:23.440 --> 1:02:25.974
I mean, (sighing)

1:02:25.976 --> 1:02:29.010
He's convinced he saw
people getting killed

1:02:29.012 --> 1:02:29.911
on this tape.

1:02:31.315 --> 1:02:33.181
And I mean, and I've
got the tape right here

1:02:33.183 --> 1:02:34.549
and it's completely blank.

1:02:35.753 --> 1:02:36.918
And I don't know what to do.

1:02:36.920 --> 1:02:39.621
I don't know if he
thinks he saw something

1:02:39.623 --> 1:02:43.291
or maybe somebody's
trying to play tricks

1:02:43.293 --> 1:02:44.092
on him or something.

1:02:47.364 --> 1:02:50.098
(sighing)

1:02:50.100 --> 1:02:52.701
Listen, I'm gonna
release him to you.

1:02:54.037 --> 1:02:57.005
But at this point, there's
nothing more I can do.

1:02:57.007 --> 1:02:58.140
- He's a good guy.

1:02:58.142 --> 1:02:59.574
- I know he's a good guy.

1:02:59.576 --> 1:03:01.843
But there's nothing
more I can do here.

1:03:05.616 --> 1:03:08.416
I would suggest just
maybe having him

1:03:08.418 --> 1:03:09.718
see a therapist.

1:03:13.690 --> 1:03:16.258
(light music)

1:03:19.863 --> 1:03:21.997
- Can I get you guys
any dessert tonight?

1:03:23.066 --> 1:03:25.500
- I think we're good, thank you.

1:03:25.502 --> 1:03:27.135
- [Waitress] Get
this out of your way.

1:03:27.137 --> 1:03:28.703
- Yeah.

1:03:28.705 --> 1:03:29.771
- Thank you.

1:03:49.226 --> 1:03:52.460
- I'm sorry you went
through all that.

