1:05:46.476 --> 1:05:47.909
- Okay, go, go ahead, pee.

1:05:47.911 --> 1:05:49.544
- Be right back, okay?

1:05:49.546 --> 1:05:51.212
- I'll be in the car.

1:05:51.214 --> 1:05:52.380
- Okay, cool.

1:06:29.786 --> 1:06:30.685
Shit.

1:06:32.389 --> 1:06:34.990
I think I left my phone
at the restaurant.

1:06:34.992 --> 1:06:36.191
- What?

1:06:36.193 --> 1:06:40.895
- I think I left my
phone at the restaurant.

1:06:47.604 --> 1:06:49.037
- Did you find a cellphone?

1:06:49.039 --> 1:06:50.638
- [Woman] I don't
know, just have a look.

1:06:50.640 --> 1:06:51.840
Is this yours?

1:06:51.842 --> 1:06:52.807
- Oh thank you.

1:06:52.809 --> 1:06:54.943
- [Woman] You're welcome.

1:06:58.615 --> 1:06:59.814
- Charles, right?

1:06:59.816 --> 1:07:00.982
- Hey there, yeah.

1:07:02.919 --> 1:07:04.119
- Billy, it was
at the lighthouse.

1:07:04.121 --> 1:07:05.286
- You and your
girlfriend, right?

1:07:05.288 --> 1:07:06.321
- Yeah.

1:07:06.323 --> 1:07:07.489
- Where's your gal?

1:07:07.491 --> 1:07:09.124
- She's back at the inn.

1:07:09.126 --> 1:07:10.959
- Well you enjoying
your stay here?

1:07:12.496 --> 1:07:16.965
- It's been a bad day today.

1:07:16.967 --> 1:07:19.067
- Oh we all have bad days.

1:07:19.069 --> 1:07:20.301
- Yeah?

1:07:20.303 --> 1:07:22.604
- Look, why don't you
join me for a drink?

1:07:22.606 --> 1:07:24.105
Come on.

1:07:24.107 --> 1:07:26.975
Sweetheart, a fresh one
and one for my friend.

1:07:26.977 --> 1:07:28.109
- [Bartender] You bet.

1:07:33.350 --> 1:07:36.951
- So, tell me all
about your bad day.

1:07:38.255 --> 1:07:40.488
Seemed like you two were
having fun at the lighthouse.

1:07:40.490 --> 1:07:42.891
- Yeah that was the
highlight of my whole stay.

1:07:44.394 --> 1:07:45.293
Great.

1:07:46.363 --> 1:07:47.262
Thank you.

1:07:48.598 --> 1:07:51.900
It's been, well,

1:07:53.203 --> 1:07:55.703
a lot of weird things going on.

1:07:57.274 --> 1:07:59.107
- [Charles] Huh,
what kind of weird?

1:08:00.477 --> 1:08:03.578
- Well, I just don't want
you to think I'm crazy,

1:08:03.580 --> 1:08:06.614
but when I was putting
clothes in my drawer,

1:08:06.616 --> 1:08:08.716
the drawer shut itself.

1:08:09.619 --> 1:08:10.585
I didn't touch it.

1:08:12.255 --> 1:08:14.355
And then this goofy thing
happened with my watch,

1:08:14.357 --> 1:08:16.057
and I lost an hour of time.

1:08:17.127 --> 1:08:19.627
Like, I don't know
where it went.

1:08:19.629 --> 1:08:24.699
And then a painting just
falling on the floor.

1:08:26.103 --> 1:08:27.402
- I guess I shouldn't
have told you

1:08:27.404 --> 1:08:29.003
that that place was haunted.

1:08:29.005 --> 1:08:30.738
- No, it's okay.

1:08:30.740 --> 1:08:32.807
I'm just learning
the hard way, thanks.

1:08:34.811 --> 1:08:36.878
- The painting
you're talking about,

1:08:36.880 --> 1:08:38.213
is it of the shipwreck?

1:08:40.317 --> 1:08:44.185
- It's a ship being tossed
around by the sea, yeah.

1:08:45.288 --> 1:08:47.122
- The ship in that painting,

1:08:47.124 --> 1:08:49.124
it's the Sir Edmund James.

1:08:49.126 --> 1:08:51.493
Remember the shipwreck I
told you about on the tour?

1:08:51.495 --> 1:08:52.961
- Ah yeah, of course, right.

1:08:54.297 --> 1:08:56.297
- Legend has it that
old Captain Louis

1:08:56.299 --> 1:08:58.266
still roams those
halls at night.

1:08:59.803 --> 1:09:02.370
It's all in that ghost
tour that I told you about.

1:09:04.407 --> 1:09:07.308
(laughing) I could
tell you scare easily.

1:09:07.310 --> 1:09:08.510
- God, well, yeah,

1:09:08.512 --> 1:09:11.146
well it's like you say,
it's just folklore.

1:09:11.148 --> 1:09:13.081
- And if you wish to
believe that sort of thing

1:09:13.083 --> 1:09:14.449
you compound the problem.

1:09:17.187 --> 1:09:18.219
- What do you mean?

1:09:20.157 --> 1:09:21.055
- Well.

1:09:22.125 --> 1:09:23.424
I'm not the sort of
person that really buys

1:09:23.426 --> 1:09:26.361
into all of the
hocus pocus stuff.

1:09:26.363 --> 1:09:27.695
But I got people who swear to me

1:09:27.697 --> 1:09:30.265
they see things in this town.

1:09:30.267 --> 1:09:31.666
- Like what?

1:09:31.668 --> 1:09:36.504
- You know, supernatural,
ghosts, sightings.

1:09:36.506 --> 1:09:38.273
Things not of this world.

1:09:40.510 --> 1:09:42.911
- Has anything ever happened

1:09:42.913 --> 1:09:44.679
in the hotel where
I'm staying at?

1:09:46.082 --> 1:09:48.349
- (chuckling) I'm sure a
lot of things have happened.

1:09:48.351 --> 1:09:51.486
It's over 150 years old,
there's a lot of history.

1:09:51.488 --> 1:09:52.387
- No, I mean,

1:09:54.457 --> 1:09:56.124
is there anything in particular?

1:09:57.694 --> 1:09:59.427
- Where are you going
with this, Billy?

1:10:04.801 --> 1:10:07.335
- I found this
videocassette under my bed

1:10:07.337 --> 1:10:08.703
and I put it in the player.

1:10:08.705 --> 1:10:10.371
And this home video comes up

1:10:11.474 --> 1:10:14.943
and it's this couple,
them driving around

1:10:14.945 --> 1:10:17.245
and then being followed
by these two guys

1:10:17.247 --> 1:10:19.147
with a video camera.

1:10:19.149 --> 1:10:22.584
And they get into some
sort of altercation.

1:10:22.586 --> 1:10:26.287
And then the video
kind of fuzzes out

1:10:26.289 --> 1:10:29.157
and a picture comes back up.

1:10:30.293 --> 1:10:33.728
And these two guys
were right in front of

1:10:33.730 --> 1:10:35.730
my hotel door.

1:10:35.732 --> 1:10:36.664
- Are you shitting me?

1:10:36.666 --> 1:10:38.733
- No, right where I'm staying.

1:10:39.803 --> 1:10:43.638
They break in and they
murder that couple.

1:10:43.640 --> 1:10:45.473
They butcher them.

1:10:50.313 --> 1:10:52.947
- That's one hell
of a story there.

1:10:56.720 --> 1:10:58.019
- Well does it sound familiar?

1:11:04.828 --> 1:11:06.094
Tell me.

1:11:06.096 --> 1:11:09.063
- Well, there have
been a few murders

1:11:09.065 --> 1:11:10.698
over the years here.

1:11:11.668 --> 1:11:13.134
- [Billy] How many is a few?

1:11:14.537 --> 1:11:15.436
- I don't know.

1:11:16.806 --> 1:11:20.942
I'd say, there's been about

1:11:20.944 --> 1:11:23.978
eight unsolved murders
in the last 40 years.

1:11:25.081 --> 1:11:27.815
The one you mentioned,
I remember it all right.

1:11:29.119 --> 1:11:32.520
It was damn grisly, those
kids they butchered.

1:11:33.490 --> 1:11:35.056
They were just a young couple.

1:11:38.461 --> 1:11:40.628
No one ever mentions it.

1:11:40.630 --> 1:11:41.796
None of it.

1:11:41.798 --> 1:11:43.197
- Well what about the cops?

1:11:44.901 --> 1:11:46.200
- Cops?

1:11:46.202 --> 1:11:47.902
They're useless.

1:11:47.904 --> 1:11:49.904
This is a one horse town.

1:11:49.906 --> 1:11:51.706
- So they didn't do
anything about it?

1:11:51.708 --> 1:11:53.007
They don't care?

1:11:53.009 --> 1:11:54.208
- Sure, they care
about keeping things

1:11:54.210 --> 1:11:56.411
like that out of the paper.

1:11:56.413 --> 1:11:58.212
Hurts the economy.

1:11:58.214 --> 1:12:00.415
Tourism is this town's
bread and butter.

1:12:05.088 --> 1:12:06.187
- When did it happen?

1:12:07.590 --> 1:12:08.489
The last one?

1:12:10.160 --> 1:12:12.827
How long ago?

1:12:12.829 --> 1:12:13.728
- Oh.

1:12:14.931 --> 1:12:17.465
I don't know, I'm
bad with dates.

1:12:17.467 --> 1:12:19.233
Plus I've been
drinking all night.

1:12:19.235 --> 1:12:20.868
- Are you sure?

1:12:20.870 --> 1:12:22.136
- Of course I'm sure.

1:12:25.842 --> 1:12:28.409
(tense music)

1:12:31.881 --> 1:12:33.414
- [Billy] What?

1:12:33.416 --> 1:12:34.315
Charles, what?

1:12:39.489 --> 1:12:41.489
- Be careful out there, Billy.

1:12:47.797 --> 1:12:50.365
(light music)

1:13:48.725 --> 1:13:51.292
(tense music)

1:13:52.328 --> 1:13:54.562
(revving)

1:13:56.666 --> 1:13:58.733
- This guy following me?

1:13:59.736 --> 1:14:01.969
(revving)

1:14:25.728 --> 1:14:30.798
(revving)
(tires screeching)

1:14:37.340 --> 1:14:38.840
What do you want?

1:14:40.109 --> 1:14:42.043
(banging)

1:14:42.045 --> 1:14:43.511
What do you want?

1:14:57.060 --> 1:14:59.293
(revving)

1:15:52.882 --> 1:15:55.216
(mumbling)

1:16:04.460 --> 1:16:06.794
(creaking)

1:16:11.734 --> 1:16:13.968
(dinging)

1:16:16.172 --> 1:16:18.372
- Hello, can I assist you?

1:16:19.208 --> 1:16:20.141
- Where's the phone?

1:16:20.143 --> 1:16:21.976
- It's behind the desk.

1:16:21.978 --> 1:16:23.044
- I need you to make a call.

1:16:23.046 --> 1:16:23.945
- Okay.

1:16:23.947 --> 1:16:24.979
Who shall I phone?

1:16:27.483 --> 1:16:29.750
- There was an
incident that happened.

1:16:29.752 --> 1:16:31.752
I need you to call the police.

1:16:31.754 --> 1:16:33.120
- What sort of an incident?

1:16:33.122 --> 1:16:35.456
- There was a car
that was following me.

1:16:35.458 --> 1:16:36.958
- That's it?

1:16:36.960 --> 1:16:38.459
Maybe they were lost.

1:16:38.461 --> 1:16:40.561
- Are all you people in on this?

1:16:40.563 --> 1:16:42.330
- What do you mean you people?

1:16:42.332 --> 1:16:45.366
Look, I'll be happy to
make the phone call,

1:16:45.368 --> 1:16:47.702
but you gotta realize one thing.

1:16:47.704 --> 1:16:51.973
It's past midnight and
there's only one car

1:16:51.975 --> 1:16:54.809
to patrol the whole island.

1:16:54.811 --> 1:16:56.510
- I don't care if
there's only one car

1:16:56.512 --> 1:16:58.813
that needs to go
patrol the goddamn zoo!

1:16:58.815 --> 1:17:01.215
I don't care, call
the fucking police!

1:17:01.217 --> 1:17:03.217
I need you to call the police!

1:17:03.219 --> 1:17:05.753
Get the phone, make
the phone call!

1:17:05.755 --> 1:17:06.821
Call!
- All right, all right!

1:17:06.823 --> 1:17:07.922
I'd be happy to do it.

1:17:07.924 --> 1:17:09.390
- Thank you!

1:17:09.392 --> 1:17:11.759
- You know, it may
take a while for them

1:17:11.761 --> 1:17:13.260
to arrive, that's all.

1:17:13.262 --> 1:17:15.963
If you want me to call
them, I'll call them.

1:17:15.965 --> 1:17:17.198
- No, no, no.

1:17:17.200 --> 1:17:18.833
No, I don't want
you to call them.

1:17:18.835 --> 1:17:20.768
I don't want you to call them.

1:17:20.770 --> 1:17:21.669
Forget it.

1:17:22.739 --> 1:17:24.672
Just forget it.

1:17:24.674 --> 1:17:26.874
- Sir, I'll be
happy to call them.

1:17:26.876 --> 1:17:28.643
It might take a while.

1:17:29.646 --> 1:17:30.544
Sir?

1:17:31.347 --> 1:17:32.246
Sir?

1:17:40.690 --> 1:17:41.756
(knocking)

1:17:41.758 --> 1:17:43.024
- [Billy] Baby, it's me.

1:17:46.262 --> 1:17:47.862
Let me in.

1:17:47.864 --> 1:17:48.763
- Coming.

1:17:51.167 --> 1:17:52.400
Hey.

1:17:52.402 --> 1:17:54.702
(creaking)

1:18:05.381 --> 1:18:06.547
- Your battery's dead.

1:18:10.286 --> 1:18:11.752
- [Lisa] Is everything okay?

1:18:14.590 --> 1:18:16.323
Billy, is everything okay?

1:18:25.501 --> 1:18:27.702
- Black car ran me off the road.

1:18:27.704 --> 1:18:31.172
It was the same car that
was at the rest stop.

1:18:31.174 --> 1:18:33.007
These are the same people

1:18:33.009 --> 1:18:34.275
that did this

1:18:34.277 --> 1:18:35.209
in the videotape.
- Okay just relax.

1:18:35.211 --> 1:18:36.711
- These are the same people

1:18:36.713 --> 1:18:39.080
and they wanna kill us,
that's what they wanna do.

1:18:55.798 --> 1:18:57.164
I went to go pick up your phone

1:18:57.166 --> 1:18:59.233
and you know that guy
at the lighthouse?

1:19:01.804 --> 1:19:02.636
- Charles.

1:19:02.638 --> 1:19:03.938
- Charles, Charles.

1:19:03.940 --> 1:19:06.207
Charles was at the restaurant.

1:19:06.209 --> 1:19:08.642
He told me that there
were murders in this town.

1:19:08.644 --> 1:19:09.744
- You're freaking me out.

1:19:09.746 --> 1:19:11.378
- Huh?

1:19:11.380 --> 1:19:12.279
They're gonna come
and murder us,

1:19:12.281 --> 1:19:13.080
'cause it's what they do.

1:19:14.117 --> 1:19:15.616
They pinpoint the
couple that comes around

1:19:15.618 --> 1:19:16.984
this time of the year
on the off season

1:19:16.986 --> 1:19:17.985
and they kill 'em.

1:19:21.924 --> 1:19:22.823
- Billy.

1:19:24.927 --> 1:19:27.261
The detective said there
was nothing on the tape.

1:19:27.263 --> 1:19:29.230
- Well, of course there's
nothing on the tape

1:19:29.232 --> 1:19:30.064
'cause that's what they do,

1:19:30.066 --> 1:19:31.298
they erase the tape.

1:19:31.300 --> 1:19:32.233
Go charge your phone.

1:19:32.235 --> 1:19:33.734
- I feel sick, I wanna go.

1:19:33.736 --> 1:19:35.369
We're going, that's
what we're doing.

1:19:35.371 --> 1:19:39.173
- We can't leave because
the tire's blown.

1:19:39.175 --> 1:19:40.274
- What?!
- The tire's blown.

1:19:40.276 --> 1:19:41.742
- What do you mean the tire?

1:19:43.045 --> 1:19:45.379
- I pulled into the
parking lot, tire's blown.

1:19:46.516 --> 1:19:47.715
- Then what about
the guy downstairs?

1:19:47.717 --> 1:19:49.483
- He's in on it too.

1:19:49.485 --> 1:19:50.584
- Well then we're
gonna call triple A,

1:19:50.586 --> 1:19:51.519
that's what we're gonna do.

1:19:51.521 --> 1:19:52.920
- Nah, we can't call triple A.

1:19:52.922 --> 1:19:54.722
Triple A can't come,
they're not gonna come now.

1:19:54.724 --> 1:19:56.290
We gotta wait till the morning.

1:19:56.292 --> 1:19:57.124
We gotta stay here.

1:19:57.126 --> 1:19:59.260
So make yourself comfy.

1:19:59.262 --> 1:20:01.162
Charge your phone,
just lie down.

1:20:02.565 --> 1:20:04.031
Just relax tonight.

1:20:22.051 --> 1:20:24.618
(tense music)

1:20:50.780 --> 1:20:53.547
(waves crashing)

1:20:58.588 --> 1:21:01.121
(tense music)

1:21:21.711 --> 1:21:24.044
(thunking)

1:21:31.053 --> 1:21:33.354
(creaking)

1:21:38.060 --> 1:21:38.959
(Lisa screaming)

1:21:38.961 --> 1:21:41.295
- [Lisa] Help, Billy, help me!

1:21:41.297 --> 1:21:43.764
- Isn't she hot, look at her!

1:21:46.202 --> 1:21:48.769
(tense music)

1:21:49.605 --> 1:21:52.239
(man laughing)

1:21:56.312 --> 1:21:59.079
Why do you fucking
bleed so much?

1:22:03.119 --> 1:22:03.984
Oh, hello.

1:22:04.921 --> 1:22:06.320
You're just in time.

1:22:06.322 --> 1:22:07.154
Come here.

1:22:07.156 --> 1:22:08.589
Wake up, asshole.

1:22:09.892 --> 1:22:12.960
(breathing heavily)

1:22:40.823 --> 1:22:41.889
- Ah, Billy.

1:22:43.059 --> 1:22:44.358
How was your stay?

1:22:44.360 --> 1:22:46.627
- I'd rather not talk about it.

1:22:46.629 --> 1:22:47.761
- Mr. Curtis.

1:22:48.798 --> 1:22:50.731
I need you to sign this please.

1:22:54.470 --> 1:22:57.471
Victor tells me that there
was a car chasing you

1:22:57.473 --> 1:23:00.074
and then you asked him
to call the police.

1:23:00.076 --> 1:23:01.976
- Yeah, it was real fun.

1:23:01.978 --> 1:23:04.244
- Well maybe it's just a
couple kids messing around,

1:23:04.246 --> 1:23:05.779
you know, with
nothing better to do.

1:23:05.781 --> 1:23:06.647
- Yeah, maybe.

1:23:07.850 --> 1:23:09.650
- Let me give you a
better pen, I'm sorry.

1:23:10.953 --> 1:23:12.186
Here, try this one.

1:23:16.092 --> 1:23:17.524
We hope to see you again

1:23:17.526 --> 1:23:20.361
and I'm sorry your stay
wasn't everything you planned.

1:23:20.363 --> 1:23:21.528
- Yeah, things happen.

1:23:42.218 --> 1:23:43.617
- (laughing) Of course, no.

1:23:43.619 --> 1:23:45.652
We look forward to
seeing you as well.

1:23:45.654 --> 1:23:46.854
See you then, bye.

1:23:48.090 --> 1:23:49.556
What's this?

1:23:49.558 --> 1:23:51.859
- The couple in room two,
they left this behind.

1:23:55.664 --> 1:23:57.197
Yeah, I guess they dropped it.

1:23:57.199 --> 1:23:58.165
Maybe you can give them a call.

1:23:58.167 --> 1:23:59.600
They'd surely want it back.

1:24:00.936 --> 1:24:02.903
- I don't think they'll need it.

1:24:02.905 --> 1:24:04.304
They won't be coming back.

1:24:09.011 --> 1:24:13.447
No.

1:24:13.449 --> 1:24:15.682
